snippet: With a temporary cease-fire expired, Israel said it had struck more than 30 targets, and militants fired almost a dozen rockets from Gaza.
abstract: Cross-border hostilities between Gaza and Israel continue one day after temporary cease-fire expires; eight Palestinians are reportedly killed in Israeli airstrikes, and Palestinian militants continue to fire rockets into Israel, but no new reports of Israeli causalities have surfaced.

byline.original: By ISABEL KERSHNER and FARES AKRAM
byline.contributor: Isabel Kershner reported from Jerusalem, and Fares Akram from Gaza.

lead_paragraph: With a temporary cease-fire expired, Israel said it had struck more than 30 targets, and militants fired almost a dozen rockets from Gaza.

headline.main: Israelis and Gazans Clash, but Fighting Is More Subdued
headline.print_headline: Gaza Clashes Continue at a Lower Level as Egypt Pushes for New Talks
